==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mammillary
<hw>Mam"mil*la*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>mammilaire</ets>. See <er>Mammilla</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to the mammilla, or nipple, or to the breast; resembling a
mammilla; mammilloid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Composed of convex convex
concretions, somewhat resembling the breasts in form; studded with small
mammiform protuberances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mammillated</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Mammillate</ent>⟦br⟧
